    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.12.19" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">29</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">JOHN MACY
                        <lb/>
                    2 FAIRMONT AVE
                        <lb/>
                    HASTINGS-ON-HUDSON
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>May 11, 1926.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Here is a delightful coincidence. I received your letter a few hours before I had a conference with Mr. Morrow about possible books. Without knowing that I was in communication with you he spoke, among other things, of the need of a book about the Indian, especially his relations with the white man. Before he had half developed his idea<add>,</add> I pulled your letter from my pocket and said: "Here is the man to do it."</p>
                
                <p>Your interest is poetic, and most of your expression is, I believe, in the form of verse. But would you not be interested to put your experiences into the form of straight prose narrative and exposition of the nature of the Indian, and perhaps go into the history of the breeds that you do not know by personal contact? If this suggestion appeals to you at all, Mr. Morrow and I will be glad to make a tentative outline (which of course you would be at liberty to discard entirely) of what, it seems to us, we and other ignorant but sympathetic people ought to be told by someone who really knows the subject and who, moreover, knows how to write as well as you do. Please let us hear from you.</p>
                
                <p>I want to see your book page, and I have no doubt that it will spread the light.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>John Macy</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
